Description: CouponCloud is a processing platform for the Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) coupon industry that enables retailers to validate and process
Full Description: CouponCloud is a processing platform for the Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) coupon industry that enables retailers to validate and process both paper and digital CPG coupons at the point of sale and receive funds directly form manufacturers in real-time without the need to sort and ship paper coupons to third party paper coupon processing plants.  Right this minute there are literally hundreds of pallets of coupons being trucked from retailers all over the country to processing plants in Texas and Mexico where they are to be hand sorted, counted and shipped back to manufacturers just so the retailers can be reimbursed for the offers. Its an extremely costly, time consuming, and antiquated system that we are able to fix with technology. CouponCloud is the first completely audit-able, end-to-end coupon validation, reconciliation and management platform for the CPG coupon industry. CouponCloud is an early stage technology startup located in Kansas City, MO currently participating in both the SparkLab KC Tech Startup Accelerator and the Rackspace.com Startup Program.  To learn more about CouponCloud or our amazing team please visit: CouponCloud.com

Description: ORA has been providing home warranty coverage, errors & omissions insurance, & real estate/.
Full Description: A home warranty is a service contract that covers the repair or replacement of many of the most frequently occurring breakdowns of home system components and appliances. Why do I need a home warranty? Your home is most likely one of your biggest investments. Unexpected repair or replacement costs can easily strain your budget. Plus, finding an approved and insured home contractor to solve your problem can be stressful and inconvenient. A home warranty cannot prevent systems or appliances from breaking down, but it can help make covered repairs or replacement easier and less costly. How does a home warranty work?
